            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir, I have you<lb/> annexed, statement of collections<lb/>
                made on a/c Occident, as well as<lb/> sales of Book's since last report<lb/>
                together amounting to Fifty 35/00. Dols<lb/> for which I hand you enclosed<lb/> my
                check on Mechanics Bank<lb/>
                <placeName>New York</placeName> less Exchange 25c for Fifty<lb/> 10/00 Dolls. I am
                pleased to learn<lb/> of the great progress you have made<lb/> in the Bibles
                completion. I have<lb/> no doubt it will prove the means<lb/> of amply repaying you
                for all your<lb/> labors bestowed in the publishing<lb/> way. Many Christians are
                anxious<lb/> to see the work, &amp; I have no a number<lb/> will be sold to
                them.</p>
            <p>We have had two discourses<lb/> delivered in our Synagogue by<lb/> our <persName>Rev
                    Mr. Jacobs</persName> in behalf of <del>our</del><lb/> suffering humanly in
                    <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Jacobs</persName> was the first Minis<lb/>ter in our city who
                suggested</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&amp; carried out this mode<lb/> of enlisting the feelings of our<lb/> citizens
                towards the pecuniary<lb/> aid of the people of our<lb/> sister city <add>?</add>
                but<lb/> a very short notice was given<lb/> through the papers, but omitted<lb/> to
                be announced on <date>Sabbath</date><lb/>
                <sic>preceeding</sic> the discourse, which<lb/> was to be on <date>Sunday</date>,
                &amp; which<lb/> omission &amp; short notice com<lb/>bined prevented a great<lb/>
                number from attending<lb/> we secured one Hundred<lb/> Dolls &amp; remitted it to
                the <add>?</add><lb/> society. Since then we have been<lb/> solicited by the
                Benevolent Society<lb/> of <add>?</add> &amp; we have from the 2d<lb/>
                <add>?</add> more to remit. So you<lb/> must admit that our <add>?</add><lb/> Hazan
                &amp; Sec<add>?</add> has done some<lb/> good by his example &amp; precepts<lb/>
                Little or but a small amt has as<lb/> yet been collected from other
                <add>?</add><lb/> I wish you would notice them<lb/>
                <add>?</add> above sealed in your next<lb/> Occident for altho our congregation<lb/>
                after the <add>?</add> and dispersed circu<lb/>lary for aid to the several
                    <placeName>North</placeName> &amp; <placeName>South</placeName><lb/> the only
                response we ever got was your Ocd<lb/>
                <add>?</add> candlesticks which I suppose your trustees<lb/> then, intended we
                should con<add>?</add> them<lb/> into gold.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>so it is. I promise myself the<lb/> pleasure of soon seeing you<lb/> perhaps spending
                the 2<lb/> days of yon <add>?</add> in your city<lb/> I wonder if <persName>Mrs
                    Himman</persName><lb/> will have room to accom<lb/>modate one? do you know<lb/>
                our city remains<add>?</add> usually<lb/> healthy, will produce<lb/> an early
                business which<lb/> compels me to leave home<lb/> earlier than is my usual<lb/>
                habit. I expect to be in<lb/> your city on <date><sic>friday</sic></date> after<lb/>
                eve of <date><sic>Roshanna</sic></date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping this will meet<lb/> you in health if not<lb/> in wealth</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">I am as always</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen</persName>
            </p>
            <p><add>?</add> &amp; all the family<lb/> join in remembrance</p>
